cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.DS, cs.SY

This paper deals with optimization for sequential decision making, which is a common theme in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on distributionally robust Markov Decision Processes, which involves uncertainty and risk management. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves statistical analysis and optimization, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
